            "organizationName": "Traditional Chinese Dance",
            "organizationProfilePicture": "3eebebba-8951-494a-999a-d1dc8021a7ed70e97eda-2f06-4db0-b480-96b045a7b908.jpg",
            "organizationNames": [],
            "name": "TCD 4TH ANNUAL SPRING SHOWCASE",
            "description": "<p>ITS TIME! \ud83e\udd41\ud83e\udd41\ud83e\udd41&hellip;For everyone&rsquo;s favorite annual showcase ever! It's time for YOU, yes YOU to immerse yourself in TCD&rsquo;s 4TH ANNUAL SHOWCASE! We are back with an expansive range of cultural dances, ranging from as soft as a spring breeze\ud83c\udf38\ud83d\udca8 to as sharp as a knife\ud83d\udd2a</p>\r\n<p>\ud83d\uddd3\ufe0f Date: May 23th, 2026<br />\ud83d\udccd Location: Kane Hall 130<br />\ud83c\udf9f\ufe0f Ticket Price: $8 for UW students, $12 for non-UW, $16 at door</p>\r\n<p>We are so honored and humbled to have the opportunity to participate in a multitude of cultural events throughout UW and the greater Seattle area. Not to downplay our previous performances, but we saved the best for last! We are so excited to finally reveal what we have been working on for the past 8 months at our showcase! Awaiting you are the beautiful solo and group dances prepared by members of TCD. Keep checking our page for updates and sneak peaks as we approach the date!\ud83c\udf1f</p>\r\n<p>BUT WAIT\u203c\ufe0f\u203c\ufe0f There is more! We are excited to announce VOLUNTEER OPPORTUNITIES!!! If you decide to lend your valuable time to us, food and drinks will be provided!\ud83c\udf55\ud83e\udd64 These will work for volunteer opportunities!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://huskylink.washington.edu/submitter/organization/tcduw/eventsubmission/docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdWoZc2iesIWU34aftjkcn6kzeuE-mEbwpvIwYGAdHOeRnHdQ/viewform\">TICKETS</a> AND <a href=\"https://huskylink.washington.edu/submitter/organization/tcduw/eventsubmission/docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfXBn0hQztqLBNUmDYI6d5-DFx7Apr376xU373DLA8FjC_8Fg/viewform\">VOLUNTEER</a> FORMS ARE LINKED HERE \ud83e\udee1 We hope to see you there\ud83d\udc97</p>\r\n<p>Thank you to our sponsors ASUW, HUB, GPSS, SAF, CSF, ECC, Alumni Association, and Office of Minority Affairs &amp; Diversity. It wouldn&rsquo;t have been possible without your support! Also a huge thank you to Coco for providing drinks for our members and volunteers!</p>\r\n<p>The University of Washington is committed to providing access, equal opportunity and reasonable accommodation in its services, programs, activities, education and employment for individuals with disabilities. To request disability accommodation contact the Disability Services Office at least ten days in advance at: 206.543.6450/V, 206.543.6452/TTY, 206.685.7264 (FAX), or e-mail at dso@u.washington.edu</p>\r\n<p>Disability Accommodations Statement: &ldquo;The University of Washington is committed to providing access, equal opportunity, and reasonable accommodations in its services, programs, activities, education, and employment for individuals with disabilities. To request disability accommodation, contact the Disability Service Office at least one day in advance by phone at 206.543.6450, 206.543.6452/TTY, 206.685.7264/FAX, or email at dso@uw.edu&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Disclaimer Statement: &ldquo;The views expressed at this program are not necessarily those of the Kelly Ethnic Cultural Center, Office of Minority Affairs &amp; Diversity, and the Services and the Activities Fee Committee.&rdquo;</p>",
